<table width="600">
	<tr>
		<td>
			<h1 align="center">Blobworld</h1>
			<hr>			
		
			<p><b>Developed by:</b><br> University of California, Berkeley </p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Features:</b><br> 
			- <u>Color</u>: Maps to 218 bins of color coordinate in Lab-space<br>
			- <u>Texture</u>: Uses mean contrast and aniosotropy over the region<br>
			- <u>Location and shape</u>: Represented in terms of area, eccentricity, and orientation
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Indexing:</b><br>
			- Color histogram projected using single value decomposition (SVD)<br>
			- Uses R*-tree data structure
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Matching:</b><br>
			- Computes quadratic distance for color.<br>
			- Computes Euclidean distance for texture.<br>
			- Combine both distance to determine similarity.
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>Querying:</b><br>
			- User select picture and give keyword, returns linear ranked pictures.  Bounce new query from results.
			</p>
			
			<p>
			<b>URL:</b> <a href="http://elib.cs.berkeley.edu/blobworld/">http://elib.cs.berkeley.edu/blobworld/</a>
			</p>
			
			<p align="center">
			<i>Fig 1. User specify shape/region to use for comparison by 
			clicking on the blob region.</i><br>
			<img border="0" src="images/blobworld/tiger_query1.jpg" width="540" height="475"></p>
			<p align="center">
			<i>Fig 2. User rate the importance of each feature.<br>
			<img border="0" src="images/blobworld/tiger_query2.jpg" width="540" height="475"></i></p>
			<p align="center">
			<i>Fig 3. Query result.&nbsp; Click on the result image to bounce 
			query.<br>
			<img border="0" src="images/blobworld/tiger_result.jpg" width="639" height="648"></i></p>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
